premise_source_doc_sentence: This assertion has been repeatedly challenged ; the largest multi-study research suggests zero or near-zero effects .

Hence , the value of SMCV is comparable whereas the value of p-value or q-value is not comparable in experiments with different sample size , especially when many investigated genes or compounds do not have exactly zero effects .

The advantage of using SMCV over p-value  (  or q-value  )  is that , if there exist any non-zero true effects for a gene or compound , the estimated SMCV goes to its population value whereas the p-value  (  or q-value  )  for testing no mean difference  (  or zero contrast mean  )  goes to zero when the sample size increases
